@bradarmstrong3952   hi, yeah the brake can tell you the stall torque with the shaft stalled.
But torque and power are different, power is;  torque × RPM. 
Power is the important unit because it represents how much electrical power you might get, ie;  measured shaft power of 10 watts, would give you maybe 7 watts of electrical power assuming the electrical generator is 70% efficient.
